comments.text:
The characters are off model and the plot is all over the place. The show is definitely weird. And yet...
I really LOVE Sonic Underground!!!
It’s so bizarre and it’s unique. I love the intro and the outro. Some of the other songs are actually GOOD (like only three but still). Yes it’s not SatAM but narrows heavily from certain plot elements. And those who bash it for being western classic Sonic and singing the praises of what few on model anime and CGI shows are there. They claim that DIC didn’t care about Sonic when they made Underground and all this bullshit. I don’t think it’s that bad and I have sensory issues that make some shows PAINFUL to watch. Sonic Underground doesn’t bother me visually and it doesn’t sound too bad most of the time. The earlier episodes sometimes have characters talking to fast and a lot of the criticism is justified but I do wish those of us who appreciate Underground for what it is can like what we like in peace. Yeah I like the “ugly” characters and think it adds charm. SatAM was just cute forest animals being terrorized by evil Jim Cummings doing his Pete voice and the bad guys are all either robots or bald. There are no ugly good guys in SatAM like in Underground. Plus there are no evil cute characters in SatAM like in Underground. Yes I’m criticizing the favorite child SatAM (which I like too btw).  I was a Sonic fan before Pokémon ever came out (yes I’m “old”) and was born before both came out. I grew up with every single DIC series and the OVA. I also watch X while I was in high school and watched a little of Boom. So I have seen a lot of Sonic. I have played a lot of Sonic too. Each Sonic series is drastically different from the other and so are the video games really. And while some of the series are better than others Sonic Underground is actually one of the best ones because it was experimental. I still have my LCD game based on it and I can vouch that the fact that I have it means that it is better than most other games I’ve played (and it’s LCD like a Game and Watch game). It’s ambitious and also very weird. It might not be everyone’s favorite Sonic series but for me it has enough charm that I have actually went and tracked down a box set of it for $3.74 on 3 discs at Walmart. I just think it’s sad that it’s that cheap because I would pay more for it if it was actually more but I am grateful for the very cheap price for the set. The worst series in my opinion is Boom but I still kinda like that one. I prefer AoStH comedy to Boom. Sorry for the rant but I’m just happy that not everyone hates Underground and that I’m not alone.
